A MAN sustained serious injuries after losing control of his car and crashing into a tree on Christo Avenue in Olivedale, Joburg on Saturday. The patient was removed using a hydraulic tool and treated on the scene by an advanced life support paramedic. Once stabilised, the patient was transported to a hospital for further care. In a separate incident, Netcare 911 responded to a crash on Winston Churchill Drive in Farningham Ridge, Pinetown, where a Nissan NP200 had lost control. Reports indicate that the driver of the bakkie lost control, resulting in a rollover down an embankment. The man sustained serious injuries and was treated on the scene by paramedics while a rescue technician used hydraulic tools to free the victim. 